Matthew Jenkins, Chief Operations Officer


Matt Jenkins joined Oportun in 2016 and serves as Chief Operations Officer. Matthew comes to Oportun from Citi, where he worked for 17 years.  During his career at Citi, Matthew held a number of leadership roles within consumer operations, most recently Managing Director and Head of Global Consumer Operations Functions.   In that role, Matthew led a team responsible for executing global strategy and achieving consistently high levels of service delivery within global operations including contact centers, collections, credit and fraud operations. During his time at Citi, Matthew helped build a workforce management and operations team that was responsible for planning and providing services to more than 100 million customers and 50,000 agents in service, collections, fraud and in the back office.  Most recently, Matthew was leading an effort to reengineer the customer interaction model to drive gains in efficiency and customer experience through automation, digitization, and optimization of the customer processes. Matthew received a B.A. in Economics, magna cum laude, from the University of Texas at Austin.



